      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Describes how a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> control animates when it opens.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>To specify a type of animation for a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph> control, set the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.PopupAnimation%2A&gt;</ph> property to one of the enumeration values.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> control gradually appears, or fades in.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This effect is created by increasing the opacity of the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> window over time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> control appears without animation.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> control scrolls from the upper-left corner of its parent.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If the screen does not provide enough room to allow the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> default behavior, the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> scrolls from the lower-right corner instead.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> control slides down or up into place.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>By default, a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> slides down.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>However, if the screen does not provide enough room for the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup"&gt;&lt;/xref&gt;</ph> to slide down, it slides up instead.</source>
        </trans-unit>
